annotationA: Phosphatidate cytidylyltransferase, photoreceptor-specific; CDP diglyceride synthetase (CdsA) is an enzyme for the synthesis of cytidine diphosphate diacylglycerol (CDP-DAG) from phosphatidic acid. CDP-DAG is the precursor of two phospholipids, phosphatidylinositol and phosphatidylglycerol. CdsA has roles in cell growth and lipid storage
annotationB: Probable cardiolipin synthase (CMP-forming); Catalyzes the synthesis of cardiolipin (CL) (diphosphatidylglycerol) by specifically transferring a phosphatidyl group from CDP-diacylglycerol to phosphatidylglycerol (PG). CL is a key phospholipid in mitochondrial membranes and plays important roles in maintaining the functional integrity and dynamics of mitochondria under both optimal and stress conditions
